---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SelectedProjects from "../components/SelectedProjects.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Henry Grantham-Smith — Software Engineer"
  description="Portfolio of Henry Grantham-Smith, MBCS: software engineering, embedded systems, backend tooling, and systems reliability projects."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">MSci Computer Science • Software Engineering • MBCS</p>
    <h1>Henry Grantham-Smith</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Software engineer interested in reliable, maintainable systems: embedded software,
      backend tooling, performance investigation, and space-adjacent engineering practice.
    </p>

    <div class="actions" aria-label="Profile links">
      <a class="button" href="/projects/">View projects</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="https://github.com/HenryGG-S" target="_blank" rel="me noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/henry-grantham-smith/" target="_blank" rel="me noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card stack" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
    <h2 id="about-heading">About</h2>
    <p>
      I have completed my MSci Computer Science programme at the University of Exeter and am
      building toward software engineering roles where correctness, documentation, and long-term
      maintainability matter.
    </p>
    <p>
      My work spans embedded C on STM32, backend and full-stack development, Haskell systems
      programming, benchmarking, and practical reliability patterns such as telemetry, command
      parsing, explicit mode management, and fault handling.
    </p>
    <p>
      I am a Professional Member of BCS, The Chartered Institute for IT (MBCS).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack" aria-labelledby="focus-heading">
    <h2 id="focus-heading">Current focus</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Embedded and systems software</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          Practising disciplined embedded development through PocketSat, including telemetry,
          command handling, mode control, sensor health checks, watchdog behaviour, and verification notes.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Maintainable application development</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          Interested in clear software structure, requirements interpretation, testing, Git-based collaboration,
          and documentation that helps real teams maintain systems over time.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Performance and reliability</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          Exploring how implementation choices affect latency, runtime behaviour, and dependable operation
          under load or constrained conditions.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack" aria-labelledby="skills-heading">
    <h2 id="skills-heading">Technical areas</h2>
    <div class="chips" aria-label="Technical skills">
      <span>Java</span>
      <span>C / Embedded C</span>
      <span>C++</span>
      <span>Python</span>
      <span>Haskell</span>
      <span>Git</span>
      <span>Linux</span>
      <span>STM32Cube/HAL</span>
      <span>PlatformIO</span>
      <span>Django</span>
      <span>React</span>
      <span>SQL / SQLite</span>
      <span>Unit and integration testing</span>
      <span>Technical documentation</span>
      <span>Telemetry and fault handling</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SelectedProjects />
</BaseLayout>
